albert howard  wikipedia albert howard from wikipedia the free encyclopedia jump to navigation search albert howard born  december  bishops castle shropshire england died  october  aged  blackheath london residence united kingdom british india nationality british fields botany alma mater university of cambridge spouse gabrielle matthaei louise matthaei sir albert howard  december  –  october  was an english botanist an organic farming pioneer and a principal figure in the early organic movement he is considered by many in the englishspeaking world to have been along with rudolf steiner and eve balfour one of the key founders of modern organic agriculture contents  life  publications  bibliography  notes  see also  references  external links lifeedit albert howard was born at bishops castle shropshire he was the son of richard howard a farmer and ann howard née kilvert he was educated at wrekin college royal college of science south kensington and as foundation scholar at st johns college cambridge in  he graduated in natural sciences at cambridge where he also obtained a diploma of agriculture in  in  he lectured in agricultural science at harrison college barbados and in  and  was a mycologist and agricultural lecturer at the imperial department of agriculture for the west indies from  he was botanist to the southeastern agricultural college wye and from – he was imperial economic botanist to the government of india in  he was created a companion of the indian empire cie and received a silver medal of the royal society of arts in  from  howard was director of the institute of plant industry indore and agricultural adviser to states in central india and rajputana he was made a fellow of the royal asiatic society in  and in  received the barclay memorial medal of that society he was knighted in  and made an honourable fellow of the imperial college of science in  howard worked in india as agricultural adviser and was in charge of a government research farm at indore he worked together with gabrielle matthaei – and her sister louise – he married gabrielle in  after her death he married louise in  gabrielle was herself a professionally trained and competent botanist and indeed the contribution of both women to organic farming is said to be underestimated howard observed and came to support traditional indian farming practices over conventional agricultural science though he journeyed to india to teach western agricultural techniques he found that the indians could in fact teach him more one important aspect he took notice of was the connection between healthy soil and the villages healthy populations livestock and crop patrick holden director of the uk soil association quoted howard as saying the health of soil plant animal and man is one and indivisible he was president of the th session of the indian science congress in  howard has been called the father of modern composting for his refinement of a traditional indian composting system into what is now known as the indore method he went on to document and develop organic farming techniques and spread his knowledge through the ukbased soil association and the rodale institute in the us his  book an agricultural testament is a classic organic farming text he emphasizes the importance of maintaining humus keeping water in the soil and the role of mycorrhiza it was his first book aimed at the general public and is his best popularly known work however his  book the waste products of agriculture based on  years of studying improved crop production in indian smallholdings is considered by some as his most important scientific publication his  book farming and gardening for health or disease was also intended for a general audience and was republished in  as the soil and health a study of organic agriculture howards work influenced and inspired many farmers and agricultural scientists who furthered the organic movement including lady eve balfour the haughley experiment the living soil and ji rodale rodale institute howard advocated studying the forest in order to farm like the forest he devoted the last half of his career to understanding that end presaging those contemporary ecologists who advocate the understanding of the interface between ecology and agriculture indeed howard is grouped along with rudolf steiner sir robert mccarrison and richard st barbe baker as one of the key progenitors of the organic agriculture movement however he says in the preface to an agricultural testament some attention has also been paid to the biodynamic methods of agriculture in holland and in great britain but i remain unconvinced that the disciples of rudolf steiner can offer any real explanation of natural laws or have yet provided any practical examples which demonstrate the value of their theories publicationsedit the following is a selection of publications by albert howard including his better known works and some lesser known publications his knighthood was conferred in  so in publications prior to that he is not referred to as sir even subsequent to that he did not always refer to himself as sir as per his contribution to nature in  and his correspondence to the british medical journal in  in the listings below as far as known in those from  onwards he is cited as sir albert howard hence his authorship is not duplicated thereafter see also external links section where further publications by him may be read online howard albert howard gabrielle lc  note on immune wheats the journal of agricultural science cambridge university press   – dois  howard albert howard gabrielle lc khan abdur rahman  the economic significance of natural crossfertilization in india india dept of agriculture memoirs botanical series vol iii no calcutta thacker spink  co london w thacker  co  published for the imperial department of agriculture in india calcutta listing at open library howard albert february  the influence of soil factors on disease resistance annals of applied biology   – doijtbx  howard albert  january  the effect of grass on trees proceedings of the royal society series b containing papers of a biological character   – jstor  doirspb  howard albert howard gabrielle lc  the development of indian agriculture india of today vol viii nd ed london humphrey milford and oxford university press retrieved  august   howard albert wad yeshwant d  the waste products of agriculture their utilization as humus oxford humphrey milford  oxford university press retrieved  august  a howard albert  february  manufacture of humus by the indore process nature   – doib retrieved  august   greenwell bernard howard albert wrench gt february  address to a meeting of the farmers club journal of the farmers club discussion held at the royal empire society craven street wc on monday  january  part   howard albert  may  medical testament on nutrition correspondence concerning the cheshire medical testament on nutrition british medical journal    doibmj  registration to view bmj articles is free howard albert  july  medical testament on nutrition correspondence british medical journal    doibmj  howard albert  an agricultural testament pdf oxford uk oxford university press archived pdf from the original on  july  retrieved  august   pdf per special rodale press edition  howard albert howard louise e  farming and gardening for health or disease subsequently published as the soil and health london faber and faber ltd retrieved  august   howard albert  introduction howard on earthworms the formation of vegetable mould through the action of worms with observation on their habits london faber and faber retrieved  august   howards introduction to the  publication of charles darwins book first published in   march  harnessing the earthworm organic gardening     april  organic campaign organic gardening     september  the animal as our farming partner organic gardening   retrieved  august    november  how to avoid a famine of quality organic gardening      first published  the soil and health a study of organic agriculture university press of kentucky isbn  retrieved  august   check date values in date help originally published by faber  faber in  as farming and gardening for health or disease bibliographyedit barton gregory  sir albert howard and the forestry roots of the organic farming movement agricultural history   – jstor  pmid  doiah  medical testament nutrition soil fertility and the national health county palatine of chester local medical and panel committee  march  retrieved  august   the subject of two letters by sir albert howard to the british medical journal  see publications section heckman j  a history of organic farming transitions from sir albert howards war in the soil to usda national organic program renewable agriculture and food systems cambridge university press   – doiraf  william lockeretz ed  organic farming an international history oxfordshire uk  cambridge massachusetts cab international cabi isbn  retrieved  august   ebook isbn  howard louise e  sir albert howard in india london faber  faber retrieved  august   pdf version rodale jj december  sir albert howard in memoriam organic gardening    sir albert howard memorial issue organic gardening magazine   september  retrieved  august   contains tributes to sir albert howard notesedit a  the online reproduction of howards  work refers to him as sir albert howard however this is an error he was not knighted until  and would not have been referred to as sir the error is an artifact of the manner in which howards name has passed into contemporary public knowledge via his two most famous books an agricultural testament first published  and soil and health first published  under a different title but known mostly by this  title by which time he was referred to as sir indeed prior to the advent of the internet and the related information explosion these were the only two works popularly known by all but the most dedicated researchers with even less known about his life history beyond brief synopses associated with the books and replicated in various book descriptions see alsoedit organic farming biodynamic agriculture compost list of sustainable agriculture topics referencesedit  a b c stinner dh  the science of organic farming in william lockeretz organic farming an international history oxfordshire uk  cambridge massachusetts cab international cabi pp – isbn  retrieved  august   ebook isbn   a b c howard louise e  sir albert howard in india london faber  faber retrieved  august   pdf version  notification of knighthood conferred  june  the london gazette no   july  retrieved  august    rebecca jones green harvest the history of organic farming and gardening in australia collingwood victoria csiro publishing  p   solomon steve sir albert howards indore method organic gardeners composting soil and health library archived from the original on  may  retrieved    a b vogt g  the origins of organic farming in william lockeretz organic farming an international history oxfordshire uk  cambridge massachusetts cab international cabi pp – isbn  retrieved  august   ebook isbn   jackson wes piper jon december  the necessary marriage between ecology and agriculture pdf ecology   – doi retrieved  august   jstor citation for page accuracy  jackson wes  natural systems agriculture a truly radical alternative pdf agricultural ecosystems and environment   – doisx retrieved  august    a b sayre laura  march  review the origins of the organic movement rodale institute retrieved  august    mantle paul two reviews see review of origins of the organic movement tributes the man of the trees richard st barbe baker p  retrieved  august    lotter dw organic agriculture j sustainable agriculture   an agricultural testament  out of print description of an agricultural testament description is verbatim from rear of dustcover cumberland books website archived from the original on  november  retrieved  august   external linksedit wikiquote h